Compiling: git clone, set up for automake, then build with ./configure and make.

Or: The program does not use any qt libraries but I use qtcreator to work on it. Use the .proj file with qtcreator.  

1. GCX uses the GTK+2.0 software tool kit which is no longer maintained. Depending on your themes some things work poorly.

2. Set up for AAVSO report: in the recipe or staredit set target and check stars in the star comments field: "target_something" will match with "check_something"


